the untimely killing of the 9th formar King Birendra on 1st June 2001. The tragic event caused a lot of changes in Nepal.

To start with the economy of the country had to be restructured due to the untimely death of the beloved king. There came a political strain and so all the political leaders of the different parties expressed their condolence to the family while demanding the reinstatement of the throne. Such conditions led to a lot of political unrest such as blockades, strikes and many demonstrations. These situations created a lot of agitation among the youth that ended in many samballong(the mixture of blood and mud ironically taken from word samchkel amongst the people of living a very dirty lifestyle).

Although many of these situations had a lot of pressure on the general public and had close ended them, it also challenged young patriots. Many young people stood up to sail into unknown situations such as cases of late night meetings with unknown people and so on. Some succeeded while others were the victims of the uncertainty.

Finally the 9th king was given a honorable6v departure and after a few weeks solidarity came into our beloved king and it was then called his 11th hour or gurun gantantra lekhba(11th hour democracy).
